author: Jeffery Martin
title: Washington and Oregon's Slowing Coronavirus Infection Rates Indicate Early Social Distancing Measures Pay Off
description: "We haven't beat this virus yet," Governor Inslee said, "and until we do, it has the potential to spread rapidly if we don't continue the measures we've put in place."
content:
With the number of new coronavirus cases beginning to decrease, evidence from both Washington and Oregon indicates that the coronavirus curve is beginning to flatten because of social distancing.
